  "title": "Magnets - attraction_repulsion of magnetic poles",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the top view of two bar magnets. Magnet 1 is horizontal with its north pole on the left and south pole on the right. Magnet 2 is to the right of magnet 1 and is vertical with its south pole at the top and north pole at the bottom.\" src=\"/images/d0ef5043b2a5cbb00a0ebfb25391a71b.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Permanent bar magnets <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> are arranged as shown in the top view diagram. Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> is fixed in place with its south pole on the right and north pole on the left. Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is free to rotate about a fixed vertical axis through its center and is initially oriented with its south pole at the top and the north pole on the bottom. Which of the following best describes whether or not Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> will rotate and provides the correct justification?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i3",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> will not rotate because the forces exerted on the two poles of Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> by the magnetic field created by Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> point in opposite directions and the torques due to those forces about the axis will cancel</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> will not rotate because Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is aligned with the magnetic field created by Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> in the orientation shown.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> will initially rotate clockwise because Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> will tend to align with the magnetic field produced by Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span></p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> will initially rotate clockwise because the force exerted on the north pole of Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> by the magnetic field created by Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> is greater in magnitude than the corresponding force exerted on the south pole of Magnet <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> in the arrangement shown.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
